State parks

• Further information: [List of Nevada state parks](/List_of_Nevada_state_parks)

Nevada's state parks are [protected areas](/Protected_area) managed by the state, including state [parks](/State_park), state [historic sites](/Historic_site), and state [recreation areas](/Recreation_area). There are 24 such units, including [Van Sickle Bi-State Park](/Van_Sickle_Bi-State_Park), which opened in July 2011 as a collaborative effort with [California](/California). [49]

