According to the 2022 [American Community Survey](/American_Community_Survey), 30.3% of Nevada's population identified as [Hispanic or Latino](/Hispanic_and_Latino_Americans) (of any race), with the largest groups being [Mexican](/Mexican_Americans) (22%), [Cuban](/Cuban_Americans) (1.5%), [Salvadoran](/Salvadoran_Americans) (1.5%), [Puerto Rican](/Stateside_Puerto_Ricans) (1%), and others (4.3%). European ancestries included [German](/German_Americans) (8.9%), [English](/English_Americans) (8.1%), [Irish](/Irish_Americans) (7.2%), and [Italian](/Italian_Americans) (4.8%). The largest Asian ancestry groups were [Filipino](/Filipino_Americans) (6.4%) and [Chinese](/Chinese_Americans) (1.9%). [64]

