[Church attendance](/Church_attendance) in Nevada is notably low, among the lowest in the U.S. A 2009 [Gallup](/Gallup_(company)) poll found only 30% of Nevadans attend church weekly or almost weekly, compared to 42% nationally. Only four states reported lower attendance. In 2020, the Public Religion Research Institute reported 67% of the population identified as Christian, a slight increase from a 2014 Pew study. [102]

According to the Pew Research Center in 2014, the major religious affiliations in Nevada were: [Protestant](/Protestantism) (35%), [Irreligious](/Irreligion) (28%), [Roman Catholic](/Catholic_Church_in_the_United_States) (25%), [Latter-day Saints](/The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints_in_Nevada) (4%), [Jewish](/Judaism) (2%), [Hindu](/Hinduism) (<1%), [Buddhist](/Buddhism) (0.5%), and [Muslim](/Islam) (~0.2%). Eastern Nevada falls within the [Mormon Corridor](/Mormon_Corridor).

In 2010, the largest denominations by adherents were the [Roman Catholic Church](/Catholic_Church_in_the_United_States) (451,070), [The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints](/The_Church_of_Jesus_Christ_of_Latter-day_Saints_in_Nevada) (175,149), and the [Southern Baptist Convention](/Southern_Baptist_Convention) (45,535). [Buddhist congregations](/Buddhism) numbered 14,727, [Baháʼí Faith](/Bah%C3%A1%CA%BC%C3%AD_Faith) had 1,723 adherents, and [Muslim](/Islam) communities totaled around 1,700. [103]

Languages

• See also: [Native American languages of Nevada](/Native_American_languages_of_Nevada)

The most common non-English languages spoken in Nevada are [Spanish](/Spanish_language), [Tagalog](/Tagalog_language), and [Chinese](/Chinese_language). [104] Indigenous languages include Northern Paiute, Southern Paiute, Shoshone, and Washo. [105]

According to U.S. Census data, the top seven non-English languages spoken in Nevada are [Spanish](/Spanish_language), [Tagalog](/Tagalog_language), [Chinese](/Chinese_language), [Vietnamese](/Vietnamese_language), [Korean](/Korean_language), [Amharic](/Amharic_language), [Arabic](/Arabic_language), and [Thai](/Thai_language). [106]

